Nigerian singer, songwriter and afro-pop sensation Buju (BNXN) is set to headline the Throne Fest Concert on April 30 at Impala grounds. The rising star and hitmaker will be the headlining act at the event sponsored by Play Entertainment, Statepen East Entertainment and Taarija Enterprises. "We are thrilled to announce the first edition of Throne Fest, featuring Nigerian sensation Buju (BNXN)," said Collins Odindo, one of the event organisers. "We couldn’t have chosen a better artiste than Buju for this edition." Buju shot to fame with the viral hit single “Spiritual” featuring Zlatan in 2019. 'The Baby Giant', as he fondly refers to himself, is famed for the hit single 'Outside', 'Feeling' featuring Ladipoe and latest Tik Tok sensation 'Finesse' by Pheelz.